comments: Wood (DET) makes marginal contact with Dinwiddie's (BKN) right arm and doesn't affect his ability to rebound.
Brown (DET) makes marginal contact with Irving's (BKN) left side/arm as he is passing the ball at the end of his drive.
Allen (BKN) makes marginal contact with his off-arm to Drummond's (DET) right arm that doesn't affect his ability to defend the shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) makes marginal body contact with Allen (BKN) during his shot attempt near the basket.
Dinwiddie (BKN) is retreating in a legal defensive position as he absorbs the body contact from Rose (DET) during his drive.
Harris (BKN) and Mykhailiuk (DET) engage and disengage with one another along the perimeter.
Irving (BKN) swipes down and makes contact with the ball prior to any further incidental contact with Rose (DET) during his drive.
Drummond (DET) delivers contact to Allen's (BKN) backside that dislodges him from position during rebounding.
Drummond (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Dinwiddie's (BKN) path and does not deliver the contact.
Irving (BKN) makes marginal body contact with Wood (DET) as he starts his dribble along the baseline.
Chandler (BKN) makes contact with the ball after it has reached its apex and is on its downward trajectory.
Harris (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Galloway's (DET) path and does not deliver the contact.
Dinwiddie (BKN) makes clean contact with the ball and incidental contact with Rose's (DET) arm thereafter during rebounding.
Harris (BKN) makes incidental contact with Rose's (DET) side as they each attempt to gain control of the loose ball.
Irving (BKN) collapses his left arm upon contact with Galloway (DET) and makes legal "high-five" contact with his right arm as Irving contests the driving shot attempt.
Chandler (BKN) makes contact with the ball after it has reached its apex and is on its downward trajectory.
Galloway (DET) and Irving (BKN) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Galloway (DET) maintains legal guarding position as body contact is made with Irving (BKN) at the end of his drive.
Galloway (DET) legally contests Irving's (BKN) jump shot attempt and would avoid making contact with Irving's right leg if it was not slightly extended.
Drummond (DET) makes contact with the ball after it has entered the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Wood (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Dinwiddie's (BKN) path and does not deliver the contact.
Mykhailiuk (DET) makes marginal contact with Dinwiddie's (BKN) side and right arm as he dribbles along the sideline.
Harris (BKN) and Galloway (DET) engage and disengage with one another along the perimeter.
Galloway (DET) contests the shot attempt to Irving's (BKN) side and makes marginal contact that does not affect his jump shot attempt or ability to follow-through naturally.
Dinwiddie (BKN) and Mykhailiuk (DET) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Harris (BKN) maintains a legal vertical position and absorbs the body contact made with Rose (DET) during his driving shot attempt.

Irving (BKN) makes marginal contact with Galloway (DET) as the two engage prior to the off-ball screen. Due to technical difficulties, the correlated clip is not uploaded at this time, but will be updated at a later date.

Allen (BKN) establishes himself in Galloway's (DET) path and absorbs the contact during the screen. Due to technical difficulties, the correlated clip is not uploaded at this time, but will be updated at a later date.
